dataset_summary: The dataset encompasses a weekly analysis of web traffic and user behavior metrics from January 1st to January 7th, 2024. On average, there were 1,543 sessions daily, with a significant count of 1,265 users, highlighting active engagement. New users comprised about a third of daily user interactions, averaging 427 new users per day. Pageviews were robust, with an average of over 6,225, indicating good site engagement and content interest. Noteworthy is the pages per session metric, which averages slightly above 4, suggesting users explored multiple pages per visit. The average session duration was roughly 2.7 minutes, implying moderate content consumption depth. The bounce rate was under 20%, indicating that a majority of the sessions involved more than one page visit, reflecting well on user engagement strategies. Conversion rates were modest at 2.78%, which could indicate potential in refining marketing strategies to bolster conversion efficacy. Daily transactions approached 34 on average, linking to a mean revenue stream of approximately $1,622, suggesting a healthy throughput in commercial conversions.
